# Font Family üÖ∞Ô∏è

The `font-family` property specifies the font for an element.

It can hold several font names as a "fallback" system. If the browser does not support the first font, it tries the next font.

```css
p {
  font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
}
```

- Start with the font you want.
- End with a **generic family** (serif, sans-serif, monospace, cursive, fantasy).

# Text Transform üî†

The `text-transform` property is used to specify uppercase and lowercase letters in a text.

- `uppercase`: CONVERTS TO ALL CAPS.
- `lowercase`: converts to all lowercase.
- `capitalize`: Capitalizes The First Letter Of Each Word.

```css
p.uppercase {
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
```

# Letter Spacing ‚ÜîÔ∏è

The `letter-spacing` property increases or decreases the space between characters in a text.

```css
h1 {
  letter-spacing: 3px;
}
h2 {
  letter-spacing: -1px;
}
```

# Text Shadow üåë

The `text-shadow` property adds shadow to text.

Syntax: `h-shadow v-shadow blur-radius color`

```css
h1 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 5px red;
}
```

Can create glowing effects (neon):
`text-shadow: 0 0 3px #FF0000;`
